Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 3B
Definition: An autosomal recessive non-syndromic intellectual disability that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the RUN and SH3 domain containing 2 gene (RUSC2) on chromosome 9p13.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1B
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the enamelin gene (ENAM) on chromosome 4q13.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 4
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta which can has_material_basis_in mutation in the DLX3 gene.
Synonym: amelogenesis imperfecta hypomaturation-hypoplastic type with taurodontism

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1A
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the beta-3 laminin gene (LAMB3) on chromosome 1q32.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 3A
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the FAM83H gene.
Synonym: autosomal dominant amelogenesis imperfecta hypocalcification type

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1C
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the enamelin gene (ENAM).
Synonym: autosomal recessive amelogenesis imperfecta local hypoplastic type

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 2A1
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the kallikrein-4 gene (KLK4) on chromosome 19q13.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1E
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in X-linked dominant mutation in the gene encoding amelogenin (AMELX).

Name: X-linked amelogenesis imperfecta hypoplastic/hypomaturation 2
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta associated with mutation in a gene in the Xq22-q28 region.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta hypomaturation type 2A2
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the matrix metalloproteinase-20 gene (MMP20).

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta hypomaturation type 2A3
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta caused  by homozygous mutation in the WDR72 gene.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta hypomaturation type 2A4
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta caused  by homozygous mutation in the C4ORF26 gene on chromosome 4q21.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta hypomaturation type 2A5
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the SLC24A4 gene on chromosome 14q32.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1H
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the integrin beta-6 gene (ITGB6) on chromosome 2q24.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1F
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the ameloblastin gene (AMBN) on chromosome 4q13.

Name: amelogenesis imperfecta type 1G
Definition: An amelogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the FAM20A gene on chromosome 17q24.
